# Proxmox resource planning (HDC)

- **Source of truth**: Treat `inventory/manual/{systems,networks,services,targets}/**/*.json` (and matching `.md`) plus `inventory/automated/systems.json` and user-provided live metrics as authoritative. Do not invent hostnames, IPs, bridges, VLANs, pool names, or cluster capacity.
- **Full workflow**: When planning or deploying a new VM or container on Proxmox, read and follow [`.cursor/skills/proxmox-resource-planning/SKILL.md`](../skills/proxmox-resource-planning/SKILL.md).
- **After capacity or topology changes**: Update the relevant sidecar `hardware` / `notes` / `access` fields, then run `node tools/hdc/cli.mjs docs lint` (see project automation rule).
- **Ops commands**: Use `node tools/hdc/cli.mjs` / `hdc.cmd` per the hdc-ops skill; never put secrets in sidecars or chat (env var names only).
